RACE.FOOTNOTES: BALLYDOOLEY (GB) got bumped at the start by the breaking outwards STANDUP and in turn bumped LANDBISCUIT, chased three then four wide coming under coaxing at the five-sixteenths, angled four to five wide into upper stretch, rallied to issue a challenge inside the final furlong knocking heads briefly inside the final sixteenth with CASH NOW before taking command in the final jumps to the finish. CASH NOW pressed the pace from the three path advancing to take command at the five-sixteenths, spun just off the inside into upper stretch, edged clear to the eighth pole, dug in under growing late threat, dueled briefly before getting displaced in the final strides to the wire. LANDBISCUIT got bumped at the start by BALLYDOOLEY due to pressure from STANDUP, chased along the inside from the tail of the field coming under coaxing at the five-sixteenths, angled out five to six wide into upper stretch and kicked on belatedly to secure the show honors. STANDUP broke out a step at the start bumping BALLYDOOLEY into LANDBISCUIT, chased just off the inside under a ride from the five-sixteenths, angled five wide into upper stretch and offered up a mild kick. MOUNT TRAVERS chased along the inside under coaxing from the five-sixteenths, spun two to three wide for home, weakened in the late stages. KLICKITAT four wide in pursuit, came under coaxing near the five-sixteenths, offered up a mild bid swinging three to four wide into upper stretch, then weakened in the late going. BUSTIN SHOUT established the front and showed the way in hand along the inside under pressure from CASH NOW to the outside, came under coaxing nearing the five-sixteenths and was headed at that station, took the inside route into upper stretch, weakened in the final furlong. PROPENSITY three wide in pursuit, came under coaxing at the five-sixteenths, angled four wide into upper stretch and tired. RUSSIAN TO WIN tracked the pace along the inside getting taken hold of intermittently when pulling on the bit at times, came under coaxing at the five-sixteenths, swung three wide into upper stretch and tired. CHOWDA chased just off the inside under coaxing from the five-sixteenths, cut the corner into upper stretch, tired.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: SPLENDID SUMMER went to the front while in the two path, was well rated while setting an uncontested pace off the rail, controlled the action while inside on the far turn, responded well when set down into upper stretch and maintained a safe advantage under steady urging. BORN A GAMBLER bumped with foes on both sides at the start, was rated just off the pace on the inside, drafted behind the leader on the far turn, was asked at the quarter-pole then tipped to the two path in upper stretch, pursued the winner under a drive to the finish and willingly earned the place. AMERICAN GRANT was caught four wide on the first turn, was reserved on the outside, came under encouragement in the three path on the far turn, was asked for his best in upper stretch, pursued the winner in the drive and lacked the needed kick while able to get the show. GHOSTLYPRINCE brushed with a rival at the start, went three wide around the opening bend, was reserved off the pace, traveled around the far turn in the two then three path, was roused four wide into the stretch, pursued the winner in the drive and also lacked the needed kick then just missed the show. PROVEN HOPE bumped with a rival at the start, was rated on the inside, saved ground through the far turn, was put to a drive in upper stretch and lacked the needed response. STRONG LIGHT bobbled in the early going, saved ground on the first turn, settled outside towards the rear on the backstretch, was roused three wide on the final turn, swung six wide into upper stretch and failed to threaten. TOGA DANCER broke out then bumped with opponents on both sides, traveled around the first turn in the two path, was unhurried near the rear, saved ground on the far turn and was no factor. GINNSU WARRIOR broke in and bumped with a foe, was taken under a tight hold early then reserved under stout restraint in the two path, leveled out some going around the far turn, was roused near the quarter-pole and failed to rally. LABARDE raced in the three path on the first turn, stalked the pace on the outside, was asked leaving the backstretch, chased in the two path on the far turn, turned into upper stretch between foes and came up empty. GOING IN STYLE brushed with a rival at the start, went four wide on the first turn, was reserved on the outside but with the benefit of the cover, was asked while three to four wide on the far turn then driven five wide into the stretch and failed to respond.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: VINDICTIVE vied briefly among a quartet before easing off to chase two to three wide with six furlongs to go, continued two to three wide through the turn coming under coaxing at the five-sixteenths, went six wide into upper stretch, dug in under a drive rallying to take command nearing the sixteenth marker, then edged clear to the finish kept to task. ANEJO broke a half a beat slow and was brushed at the start by NO BURN breaking outwards, chased along the inside from the tail of the field, tipped out three wide midway on the turn, then went four wide put to coaxing five-sixteenths from home, angled seven wide into upper stretch and kept on one paced to the finish to procure the show honors. MARKET ALERT vied early on inside a trio before easing off to chase inside, came under coaxing just off the inside at the three-eighths, angled four to five wide into upper stretch and weakened. NO BURN broke out at the start brushing ANEJO, vied briefly with three rivals before emerging to duel with EMPTY TOMB to the outside while three then two wide, tucked inside five furlongs from home, came under coaxing midway on the turn when in the midst of being shaken off by his main pace rival, spun just off the inside into upper stretch in retreat and folded in the drive.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: Vagrancy S. - Grade3 BELMONT PARK RACE 8 6 1/2F Dirt CR: 106. Stakes Purse 175000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES FOUR YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD. Non-Lasix Race pursuant to 4043.2 (7)(e)(5) Lasix not permitted within 48 hours of post time. By subscription of $175 each which should accompany the nomination; $875 to pass the entry box and an additiona l $875 to start. For horses not originally nominated, a supplemental payment of $875 in addition to the entry and starting fees may be made at any time prior to the closing of entries. The purse to be divided 55% to the owner of the winner, 20% to second , 12% to third, 6% to fourth, 4% to fifth and 3% divided equally amongst the remaining finishers. Weight, 124. Non-winners of a Graded sweepstakes since August 1, 2022 allowed 2 lbs.; of a sweepstakes other than state-bred in 2023 allowed 4 lbs.; of two r aces other than maiden, claiming, starter or state-bred allowance allowed 6 lbs. A trophy will be presented to the winning owner. Closed Saturday, April 29, 2023 with 20 Nominations.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: CARAMEL SWIRL settled off the pace, dropped back near the nine-sixteenths, drafted behind foes while three then four wide on the turn, was roused five wide into the stretch, accelerated quickly while rallying on the outside, closed fast to get the lead outside the sixteenth-pole then glided clear while eased up. DR B tracked the pace on the inside of a foe, lost position badly in the two path on the turn then dropped to the rear inside the three-eighths, shifted three then four wide from behind foes while asked late on that bend, came six wide into the stretch and reached her best stride too late while finishing with good courage for the place. ROSSA VELOCE was hustled to the front, showed the way with some company to her outside, vied in the two path on the turn, shook clear outside the five-sixteenths, was asked for her best into upper stretch, led under a drive until outside the sixteenth-pole then was overtaken while clear for the show. MOSIENKO broke out then brushed with a foe, settled off the pace, moved closer near the nine-sixteenths, chased four wide early on the turn, made a bid at the three-eighths, dropped to the three path under urging near the quarter-pole, pursued the leader under a drive into the final furlong and weakened. MIDNIGHT STROLL bumped lightly with a foe at the start and was last to commence, settled on the outside, gained late on the backstretch, chased five wide on the turn, dropped to the four path nearing the quarter-pole, pursued the leader under a drive into the final furlong and tired. FUNNY HOW was restless in the gate, settled just off the pace on the inside, was roused near the three-eighths, saved ground into the stretch and came up empty. EASY TO BLESS bumped lightly with a rival at the start, moved up then prompted the pace on the outside of the leader, vied in the three path on the turn, dropped back with three furlongs to run and capitulated.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: BELMONT PARK RACE 9 6F Inner turf CR: 70. Maiden Claiming Purse 47000. INNER TURF (UP TO $8,178 NYSBFOA) FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. RACE.FOOTNOTES: CYNWYD established the front and showed the way in hand just off the inside, came under coaxing near the quarter pole, continued just off the inside into upper stretch, edged clear under a drive kept to task. THE COMPAS MAN (IRE) three to four wide in pursuit, came under coaxing at the three-eighths, spun three wide for home and ran on to chase the winner home just preserving the place honors on the wire over a closing rival. BILLY'S GOT ISSUES broke in at the start bumping SWAY'SINMYDNA, chased four then three wide under coaxing from the five-sixteenths, angled four wide into upper stretch and offered up a mild kick. SWAY'SINMYDNA bobbled at the break and was bumped by the aforementioned foe, chased two to three wide coming under coaxing at the five-sixteenths, angled five wide into upper stretch and kept on to the finish. THEREGOESMYMIRACLE chased along the inside coming under coaxing at the five-sixteenths, swung three wide for home advancing, then made no late headway through the final furlong. OXFORD UNION two to three wide in pursuit from near the rear of the field, came under coaxing at the three-eighths, angled out eight wide into upper stretch and passed tired rivals. NIEUWENDYK away to an awkward start, chased along the inside under coaxing from the five-sixteenths, spun just off the inside into upper stretch and offered no response. BEAR'S CORRECT chased three then two wide under coaxing from the five-sixteenths, angled out seven wide into upper stretch, tired. EDDIEMUSH shied in at the start in reaction to WEALLLIKEDHIM breaking inwards and was away last, strode green and sluggish four to five paths off the inside down the backstretch growing detached at the tail of the field, tucked three wide through the turn, went four wide at the head of the stretch and made no impact. FATHER OF LIES chased five then four wide under coaxing from the three-eighths, briefly tucked to the two path with five-sixteenths to go before angling five wide into upper stretch and tired. CARPE CAPELLA chased along the inside under coaxing from the five-sixteenths, spun just off the inside into upper stretch and tired. WEALLLIKEDHIM broke in at the start, chased five then four wide under coaxing from the three-eighths, went seven to eight wide into upper stretch and faltered.
